# MASTER SERVICES AGREEMENT This Master Services Agreement (the "Agreement") is entered into as of [Date], by and between The Westervelt Company, an Alabama corporation with offices at [Address] ("Westervelt"), and [Contractor Name], a [State] [Entity Type] with offices at [Address] ("Contractor"). ## RECITALS WHEREAS, Westervelt desires to retain Contractor from time to time to perform certain work and/or services in connection with its operations; and WHEREAS, Contractor is engaged in the business of providing such services and desires to perform such services for Westervelt, subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. ## 1. SCOPE OF WORK This Agreement establishes a framework for the performance of work and services (the "Work"). Specific details regarding the Work shall be set forth in individual Work Orders executed by the parties. Each Work Order shall specify the scope, deliverables, schedule, compensation, and any additional terms. No Work shall be performed until a Work Order has been executed by both parties. ## 2. TERM This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and continue for a period of one (1) year, unless earlier terminated in accordance with this Agreement. This Agreement shall automatically renew for successive one (1) year terms unless either party provides written notice of non-renewal at least thirty (30) days prior to the expiration of the then-current term. ## 3. PAYMENT TERMS Contractor shall be compensated as set forth in each Work Order. Payments shall be subject to inspection, acceptance, and receipt of lien waivers. Westervelt shall not be obligated to make more than one (1) payment per month. Final payment shall not be due until Contractor delivers evidence satisfactory to Westervelt that all subcontractors and suppliers have been paid in full and all lien waivers have been executed. ## 4. SAFETY AND COMPLIANCE Contractor shall comply with all applicable federal, state, and local laws, ordinances, and regulations, including OSHA and all environmental laws. Contractor shall be solely responsible for the safety and health of its employees and subcontractors, and for maintaining the Work site in a safe condition. Contractor shall indemnify and hold harmless Westervelt from any fines, penalties, or damages arising from Contractor's failure to comply with safety or environmental requirements. ## 5. INSURANCE Contractor shall maintain, at its own expense, insurance coverage as described in Exhibit B, including but not limited to Workers' Compensation, Employer's Liability, Commercial General Liability, Automobile Liability, Pollution Liability, and Umbrella coverage. Westervelt shall be named as an additional insured on all required policies. Contractor shall provide certificates of insurance prior to commencing Work. ## 6. INDEMNIFICATION To the fullest extent permitted by law, Contractor shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Westervelt, its officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any and all claims, damages, losses, and expenses, including attorneys' fees, arising out of or related to the performance of the Work, except to the extent caused by the sole negligence of Westervelt. ## 7. CONFIDENTIALITY & DATA SECURITY Contractor shall maintain in strict confidence all information provided by Westervelt or developed in the course of performing the Work, including without limitation business, financial, technical, and operational information. Contractor shall implement commercially reasonable safeguards to protect Westervelt's confidential information and electronic systems from unauthorized access, disclosure, or use. ## 8. SUBCONTRACTORS Contractor shall not subcontract any portion of the Work without Westervelt's prior written consent. All subcontractors must agree to be bound by the terms of this Agreement and must maintain insurance coverages equivalent to those required of Contractor. ## 9. AUDIT RIGHTS Westervelt shall have the right, upon reasonable notice, to audit Contractor's records related to the Work, including payroll, safety, insurance, and subcontractor payments, to verify compliance with this Agreement. ## 10. TERMINATION Westervelt may terminate this Agreement or any Work Order for cause upon written notice if Contractor fails to perform in accordance with this Agreement. Westervelt may also terminate for convenience upon ten (10) days' written notice. In such event, Contractor shall be entitled to payment for Work performed to date, less any damages. ## 11. DISPUTE RESOLUTION The parties shall first attempt to resolve any dispute through good faith negotiations between senior executives. If not resolved, the dispute shall proceed to non-binding mediation before a mutually agreed mediator in Alabama. If still unresolved, either party may bring suit in the state or federal courts of Tuscaloosa County, Alabama. ## 12. MISCELLANEOUS This Agreement shall be governed by and construed under the laws of the State of Alabama. This Agreement may not be assigned by either party without prior written consent. If any provision is held invalid, the remaining provisions shall remain in effect. IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement as of the Effective Date:
THE WESTERVELT COMPANY [CONTRACTOR NAME]
